            <p>I just tweaked a script for some quick and easy cross-linking between posts (<a href="https://actions.getdrafts.com/a/11Q" class="inline-onebox">Cross link drafts | Drafts Action Directory</a>). That got me wondering how many other people are using Drafts as a knowledge management base, and whether anyone had any tips or tricks to share.</p>
<p>I’m drawing on thoughts from things like <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/T382CLwAjsy3fmecf/how-to-take-smart-notes-ahrens-2017">How to take smart notes (Ahrens, 2017)</a> and <a href="https://roamresearch.com/#/v8/help/page/Vu1MmjinS">the Roam research white paper</a> (which is in itself an intriguing proposition but still in the early days of its development).</p>
<p>I know there are other apps for this kind of thinking (DevonThink, Evernote, even Notion, etc), but having tried most/all of them over the years, I’m still very comfortable in Drafts. Just curious to know if anyone else is doing anything that I might be able to learn from.</p>
<p>Any and all thoughts gratefully received.</p>
