          <title>Drafts 2021: Year in Review</title>
          <dc:creator><![CDATA[agiletortoise]]></dc:creator>
          <category>News &amp; Updates</category>
          <description><![CDATA[
            <p>2021 has been a busy year for Drafts. I am, generally speaking, a person who prefers to spend their time contemplating the present and future, but it’s not a bad idea to look back now and then and remind yourself of what you have accomplished.</p>
<p>In case you missed some of it, here are a few of the major features that have made their way into Drafts in 2021:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://docs.getdrafts.com/extending/">Custom Syntaxes and Themes</a></li>
<li>
<a href="https://forums.getdrafts.com/t/using-google-task-with-drafts/10575">Google Task</a> and <a href="https://forums.getdrafts.com/t/using-drafts-with-microsoft-to-do/10574">Microsoft To Do</a> Integration</li>
<li>
<a href="https://docs.getdrafts.com/docs/extensions/widgets">Widget</a> Theming</li>
<li><a href="https://docs.getdrafts.com/docs/editor/document-scanning">Document Scanning and Live Text Support</a></li>
<li><a href="https://docs.getdrafts.com/docs/settings/bookmarks">Folder Bookmarks</a></li>
<li><a href="https://docs.getdrafts.com/docs/automation/shortcuts">Shortcuts Support on Mac</a></li>
<li><a href="https://docs.getdrafts.com/docs/extensions/applewatch">New Apple Watch App</a></li>
<li><a href="https://docs.getdrafts.com/docs/editor/autocomplete#syntax-specific-autocomplete-suggestions">Auto-Complete for <code>[[Wiki-Style]]</code> Links</a></li>
<li><a href="https://docs.getdrafts.com/docs/editor/autocomplete#global-autocomplete-suggestions">Global Auto-Complete Suggestions</a></li>
<li><a href="https://docs.getdrafts.com/docs/editor/transcription">Transcription of Audio and Video Files</a></li>
<li><a href="https://docs.getdrafts.com/docs/editor/document-scanning#extracting-text-from-pdf-files">Extract Text from PDFs</a></li>
</ul>
<p>I would like to thank everyone who uses Drafts, those that support the app with a Pro subscription, and all the great community members who share their time and creative solutions with others – both on this forum and elsewhere!</p>
<p>I don’t like to be too specific about future plans, but we have a lot of good things coming in 2022…including celebrating the 10th anniversary of Drafts’ original 1.0 release (Yikes!).</p>
<p>Here’s hoping 2022 is great for you and yours, and thanks again for using Drafts!</p>
