        <item>
          <title>Quick Journaling - Write stuff in Today’s Journal and act on it later</title>
          <dc:creator><![CDATA[kirk]]></dc:creator>
          <category>Actions - Share What You&#39;ve Made</category>
          <description><![CDATA[
            <p>The short version is that I like the idea of bullet journals, but in practice I’d much rather log things in my phone or watch than with a pen and paper. I also want the things I’ve written to automatically go to my calendar and task manager, instead of having to sit down with a paper journal and manually transcribe them.</p>
<p>This action group lets me easily:</p>
<ul>
<li>Go to Today’s Journal</li>
<li>Append the current draft to Today’s Journal</li>
<li>Process journal events and send them to Fantastical, OmniFocus, and Day One</li>
</ul>
<p>I hope someone else finds this to be useful!</p>
<p>Find it at <a href="https://actions.getdrafts.com/g/1Sd" rel="nofollow noopener">https://actions.getdrafts.com/g/1Sd</a></p>
